    <abstract>
      <t>Segment Routing is a source routing paradigm that explicitly indicates the forwarding path for packets at the ingress node. An SR Policy is associated with one or more candidate paths, and each candidate path is either dynamic, explicit, or composite. This document describes SR policy Group in MPLS and IPv6 environments and illustrates some use cases for parent SR policy and SR Policy Group to provide best practice cases for operators</t>
